Watch out for<p><pre><code>    for (var prop in obj) {}
</code></pre>
It may iterate over attributes defined in the objects prototype. The right way to iterate over an object is<p><pre><code>    for(var prop in obj) {
        if(obj.hasOwnProperty(prop))
            doSomethingWith(obj[prop]);
    }
</code></pre>
(see <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/a/588276" rel="nofollow">http://stackoverflow.com/a/588276</a>)
